<paragraph id="IAS19_BC262" base="F16152492" principles="no"><paranum>BC262</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 19"/><data name="paranum" value="BC262"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS19_P1667" outputclass="keep_with_next">In finalising the amendments made in 2011, the Board decided that an entity should:</p><ol id="IAS19_L0204" base="F16152494" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IAS19_P1668" base="F16152495">recognise a plan amendment or curtailment when it occurs (<xref id="IAS19_X1123" base="F16231080" href="IAS19_gBC154-BC159.dita#IAS19_gBC154-BC159">paragraphs BC154&#x2013;BC159</xref>); and</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IAS19_P1669" base="F16152497">recognise termination benefits when the entity can no longer withdraw the offer of those benefits (<xref id="IAS19_X1124" base="F16231081" href="IAS19_gBC258-BC260.dita#IAS19_gBC258-BC260">paragraphs BC258&#x2013;BC260</xref>).</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>